cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SD 

The paper proposes an unsupervised learning technique using neural networks for pattern classification, which falls under the category of machine learning. The use of neural networks and clustering algorithms suggests that the paper could belong to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on image patterns and dimensionality reduction suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of unsupervised learning and clustering algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
